organization.description: The Federal Laboratory Consortium for Technology Transfer (FLC) is the nationwide network of federal laboratories that provides the forum to develop strategies and opportunities for linking laboratory mission technologies and expertise with the marketplace.
organization.title: Federal Laboratory Consortium
organization.name: federal-laboratory-consortium

extras.value: Capabilities:   Multispectral imaging radiometers and spectrometers to collect imagery and spectral data across the electromagnetic spectrum. Emphasis on the 3 to 5 and 8 to 12 micron ranges in the infrared; visible, both photopic and color, near infrared to 1.09 microns; 35 and 95 GHz millimeter wave radar.    Millimeter wave radar capabilities augmented by the co-located capabilities of the Army Research Laboratory    Calibration sources available across the spectral regions    Includes an instrument lift on a 120&#39; tower    Includes two turntables, each with capacity exceeding 70 tons; one emplaced and the other repositionable    Associated data-handling laboratory produces multispectral databases with embedded images. Product is deliverable in PC-based format compatible with common office software    Perception laboratory creates and operates image-based scenarios, both static and moving, for determining detection parameters    Provides home base for geographically mobile field perception studies, including environmentally conditioned booths accommodating up to 24 observers    Provides support for acoustic signature collection with three-dimensional arrays of high-resolution analysis
